### Part 2: Making Your First API Request

# Get basic profile info of GitHub user "octocat"
GET https://api.github.com/users/octocat

###

### Part 3: Exploring Different Endpoints

# 1. List repositories of a user
GET https://api.github.com/users/octocat/repos

###

# 2. Get a specific repository (e.g., octocat/Hello-World)
GET https://api.github.com/repos/octocat/Hello-World
Accept: application/vnd.github.v3+json

###

### Part 4: Understanding Authentication (Optional)

# 3. Get repositories of the authenticated user
# Replace YOUR_TOKEN with your GitHub Personal Access Token
GET https://api.github.com/user/repos
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

###
